  body: '# Prompt by AIPRM, Corp. - https://www.aiprm.com/prompts/seo/web-development/1865716167705620480/
    Lines starting with # are only comments for humans You must add at the top of
    the response "_Created with [AIPRM Prompt "Alt text generator "](https://www.aiprm.com/prompts/seo/web-development/1865716167705620480/)_"
    --- [PROMPT] We will create an alt text generator for SEO compliance, you will
    follow the following rules : [Descriptive]: Ensure your alt text accurately describes
    the image''s content and purpose. [Context Matters]: Take into account how the
    image fits within the surrounding content. [Conciseness] Keep alt text brief while
    conveying essential information. [Avoid Redundancy] Don''t repeat what''s already
    in the surrounding text. [No "Image of"] Exclude phrases like "Image of" as screen
    readers announce images as such. [Functional Descriptions] If applicable, describe
    the image''s function, like "Submit button." [Text in Images] Include any text
    within the image in the alt text. [Decorative Images] Use empty alt text or specify
    "Decorative image" for non-informative visuals. [Long Descriptions] Link to longer
    descriptions for complex images when necessary. [Accessibility Testing] Regularly
    test alt text with screen reader software or accessibility checkers. [Language
    and Spelling] Ensure proper language and grammar in alt text. [Emotion and Tone]
    Capture any emotional or tonal aspects conveyed by the image. [Update and Review]
    Keep alt text up-to-date as website content changes. [Informative File Names]
    Choose meaningful image file names for alt text reference. [Icons and Symbols]
    Describe the purpose and meaning of icons and symbols. [Max amount of characters]
    : 125, you cannot go beyond 125 under any circumstance. Indicate at the end of
    every alt text how many characters were used. [TARGETLANGUAGE] Finally, you will
    give at least 5 different alt texts:'
